    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Feature description\r\n\r\nit would be great if vim.ui.input would allow to input secrets, like the vim builtin `inputsecret` -- meaning a text input, but * gets displayed instead of real characters when you type.\r\n\r\nI'm using nvim neogit to work with git, and the first time I need to use git, I must enter my git passphrase. neogit asks through vim.inputsecret -- there is no other option that I know of -- and I many times don't notice the prompt at the bottom of the screen. With a hypothetical vim.ui.inputsecret and a library like dressing.nvim, the issue would be solved, since dressing.nvim is a lot more \"in your face\".\r\nProbably it should be a new call vim.ui.inputsecret rather than a flag to vim.ui.input, because if libraries that reimplement the UI like dressing.nvim don't have support for the flag at first, it could be a security issue.\r\n\r\nAnyway, just an idea, feel free to close ofc.",
